                        "content": "The nurse is assessing a client's muscle strength. The nurse asks the client to hold the arms up and supinated, as if holding a tray, and then asks the client to close the eyes. The client's left hand turns and moves downward slightly. The nurse interprets this to mean that the client has which condition?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nPronator drift occurs when a client cannot maintain the hands in a supinated position with the arms extended and the eyes closed. This assessment may be done to detect small changes in muscle strength that might not otherwise be noted. Ataxia is a disturbance in gait. Nystagmus is characterized by fine, involuntary eye movements. Hyperreflexia is an excessive reflex action.\n\nClient Needs: Physiological Integrity\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Recognize Cues\nCognitive Ability: Analyzing\nContent Area: Health Assessment/Physical Exam: Musculoskeletal\nIntegrated Process: Nursing Process/Assessment\nPriority Concepts: Functional Ability, Clinical Judgment\nStrategies: Subject\n   Test-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, techniques for assessing muscle strength. Looking at everyday meanings of words is a useful strategy that may help you with this question. The word drift means to move slightly or without effort; knowing this will assist in directing you to the correct option.\n \n   ",
                        "id": "f1b566d836784d569e8098d7fa581384",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
