                        "type": "1",
                        "version": 0,
                        "content": "The nurse is performing a physical assessment of a client's musculoskeletal system and notes that the client is right-handed. The nurse would document which assessment findings as normal? Select all that apply.",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "11797937e327eb6d913faa80427c566b",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Analyzing 分析",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nFasciculations are fine muscle twitches that normally are not present. Muscle strength is graded from 0/5 (paralysis) to 5/5 (normal power). Symmetrical muscle movement is a normal finding. Hypertrophy, or increased muscle size, on the client's dominant side of up to 1 cm is considered normal.\n\nClient Needs: Health Promotion and Maintenance\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Take Action\nCognitive Ability: Analyzing\nContent Area: Health Assessment/Physical Exam: Musculoskeletal\nIntegrated Process: Communication and Documentation\nPriority Concepts: Functional Ability, Clinical Judgment\nStrategies: Subject\n   Test-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, normal findings during a physical assessment of the musculoskeletal system. Read each option carefully and think about the normal musculoskeletal findings. Noting that the client's dominant side is the right side will assist in answering correctly.\n \n   ",
                        "id": "a0ee84bc2d984ec3a8a924ddb0e47b02",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    }
